sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as RHOAI Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Proxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>Auth Enforcement
    participant VLLM_HTTP as vLLM HTTP API<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant VLLM_GRPC as vLLM TGIS gRPC<br/>8033/TCP gRPC
    participant GPU as NVIDIA GPU<br/>CUDA
    participant Storage as Model Storage<br/>S3 / HuggingFace<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over VLLM_HTTP,Storage: Flow 3: Model Loading at Startup
    VLLM_HTTP->>Storage: GET model weights<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / AWS IAM
    Storage-->>VLLM_HTTP: Model artifacts
    VLLM_HTTP->>GPU: Load model to VRAM<br/>CUDA API

    Note over Client,GPU: Flow 1: HTTP Model Inference Request (OpenAI-Compatible)
    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Gateway->>Proxy: Forward request
    Proxy->>VLLM_HTTP: HTTP/8000<br/>Plaintext (pod-internal)<br/>Auth: Verified by proxy
    VLLM_HTTP->>GPU: Inference compute<br/>CUDA API
    GPU-->>VLLM_HTTP: Inference result
    VLLM_HTTP-->>Proxy: JSON response
    Proxy-->>Gateway: Forward response
    Gateway-->>Client: HTTPS response

    Note over VLLM_GRPC,GPU: Flow 2: gRPC Inference (TGIS Protocol)
    participant InternalSvc as Internal Service
    InternalSvc->>VLLM_GRPC: gRPC GenerationService<br/>8033/TCP, Plaintext<br/>Auth: None (cluster-internal)
    VLLM_GRPC->>GPU: Inference compute<br/>CUDA API
    GPU-->>VLLM_GRPC: Inference result
    VLLM_GRPC-->>InternalSvc: gRPC response
